This paper deals with the power consumption analysis of Carrier Aggregation (CA) in LTE-Advanced mobile networks. The topic is related to network infrastructure (NI) and mobile applications (MA) as it involves the performance of user equipment. The paper also incorporates a context-aware power consumption model, which falls under the category of systems and control (SY) and information theory (IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of CA on power consumption, which is relevant to cryptography and security (CR) as it affects the battery life of mobile devices.
